  "text": "at ASPET Journals on June 22, 2017 dmd.aspetjournals.org droxylated anywhere on the alkyl chain, and a metabolite with the molecular formula of C 12 H 22 N 2 OS and an accurate mass of 243.1488 Da. Only the UTB metabolite was mentioned as a male rat metabolite in the earlier literature [CITATION_1] . To our knowledge, the other metabolites have not been found before in either in vivo or in vitro studies. This can be explained by the duration of the experiment. The metabolites were detected in a small amount after 24 h, whereas most in vitro experiments are not carried out for more then a few hours. Moreover, enzyme activities are more stable in the sandwich culture compared with other in vitro systems, and both phase I and II metabolic pathways remain intact. This explains why incomplete recovery of the mass balance was not reported by [CITATION_2] .",
